09802 /**
09803  * cvmx_gmx#_rx#_udd_skp
09804  *
09805  * GMX_RX_UDD_SKP = Amount of User-defined data before the start of the L2 data
09806  *
09807  *
09808  * Notes:
09809  * (1) The skip bytes are part of the packet and will be sent down the NCB
09810  *     packet interface and will be handled by PKI.
09811  *
09812  * (2) The system can determine if the UDD bytes are included in the FCS check
09813  *     by using the FCSSEL field - if the FCS check is enabled.
09814  *
09815  * (3) Assume that the preamble/sfd is always at the start of the frame - even
09816  *     before UDD bytes.  In most cases, there will be no preamble in these
09817  *     cases since it will be packet interface in direct communication to
09818  *     another packet interface (MAC to MAC) without a PHY involved.
09819  *
09820  * (4) We can still do address filtering and control packet filtering is the
09821  *     user desires.
09822  *
09823  * (5) UDD_SKP must be 0 in half-duplex operation unless
09824  *     GMX_RX_FRM_CTL[PRE_CHK] is clear.  If GMX_RX_FRM_CTL[PRE_CHK] is clear,
09825  *     then UDD_SKP will normally be 8.
09826  *
09827  * (6) In all cases, the UDD bytes will be sent down the packet interface as
09828  *     part of the packet.  The UDD bytes are never stripped from the actual
09829  *     packet.
09830  *
09831  * (7) If LEN != 0, then GMX_RX_FRM_CHK[LENERR] will be disabled and GMX_RX_INT_REG[LENERR] will be zero
09832  */
09833 union cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp {
09834     uint64_t u64;
09835     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s {
09836 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
09837     uint64_t reserved_9_63                : 55;
09838     uint64_t fcssel                       : 1;  /**< Include the skip bytes in the FCS calculation
09839                                                          0 = all skip bytes are included in FCS
09840                                                          1 = the skip bytes are not included in FCS
09841                                                          When GMX_TX_XAUI_CTL[HG_EN] is set, FCSSEL must
09842                                                          be zero. */
09843     uint64_t reserved_7_7                 : 1;
09844     uint64_t len                          : 7;  /**< Amount of User-defined data before the start of
09845                                                          the L2 data.  Zero means L2 comes first.
09846                                                          Max value is 64.
09847                                                          When GMX_TX_XAUI_CTL[HG_EN] is set, LEN must be
09848                                                          set to 12 or 16 (depending on HiGig header size)
09849                                                          to account for the HiGig header. LEN=12 selects
09850                                                          HiGig/HiGig+, and LEN=16 selects HiGig2. */
09851 #else
09852     uint64_t len                          : 7;
09853     uint64_t reserved_7_7                 : 1;
09854     uint64_t fcssel                       : 1;
09855     uint64_t reserved_9_63                : 55;
09856 #endif
09857     } s;
09858     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn30xx;
09859     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn31xx;
09860     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn38xx;
09861     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn38xxp2;
09862     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn50xx;
09863     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn52xx;
09864     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn52xxp1;
09865     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn56xx;
09866     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn56xxp1;
09867     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn58xx;
09868     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn58xxp1;
09869     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn61xx;
09870     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn63xx;
09871     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn63xxp1;
09872     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn66xx;
09873     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn68xx;
09874     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn68xxp1;
09875     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn70xx;
09876     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cn70xxp1;
09877     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_s        cnf71xx;
09878 };
09879 typedef union cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp cvmx_gmxx_rxx_udd_skp_t;
09880 
09881 /**
09882  * cvmx_gmx#_rx_bp_drop#
09883  *
09884  * GMX_RX_BP_DROP = FIFO mark for packet drop
09885  *
09886  *
09887  * Notes:
09888  * The actual watermark is dynamic with respect to the GMX_RX_PRTS
09889  * register.  The GMX_RX_PRTS controls the depth of the port's
09890  * FIFO so as ports are added or removed, the drop point may change.
09891  *
09892  * In XAUI mode prt0 is used for checking.
09893  */
09894 union cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx {
09895     uint64_t u64;
09896     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s {
09897 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
09898     uint64_t reserved_6_63                : 58;
09899     uint64_t mark                         : 6;  /**< Number of 8B ticks to reserve in the RX FIFO.
09900                                                          When the FIFO exceeds this count, packets will
09901                                                          be dropped and not buffered.
09902                                                          MARK should typically be programmed to ports+1.
09903                                                          Failure to program correctly can lead to system
09904                                                          instability. */
09905 #else
09906     uint64_t mark                         : 6;
09907     uint64_t reserved_6_63                : 58;
09908 #endif
09909     } s;
09910     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn30xx;
09911     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn31xx;
09912     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn38xx;
09913     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn38xxp2;
09914     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn50xx;
09915     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn52xx;
09916     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn52xxp1;
09917     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn56xx;
09918     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn56xxp1;
09919     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn58xx;
09920     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn58xxp1;
09921     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn61xx;
09922     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn63xx;
09923     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn63xxp1;
09924     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn66xx;
09925     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn68xx;
09926     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn68xxp1;
09927     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn70xx;
09928     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cn70xxp1;
09929     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_s        cnf71xx;
09930 };
09931 typedef union cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_dropx_t;

09933 /**
09934  * cvmx_gmx#_rx_bp_off#
09935  *
09936  * GMX_RX_BP_OFF = Lowater mark for packet drop
09937  *
09938  *
09939  * Notes:
09940  * In XAUI mode, prt0 is used for checking.
09941  *
09942  */
09943 union cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_offx {
09944     uint64_t u64;
09945     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_bp_offx_s {
09946 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
09947     uint64_t reserved_6_63                : 58;
09948     uint64_t mark                         : 6;  /**< Water mark (8B ticks) to deassert backpressure */
09949 #else
09950     uint64_t mark                         : 6;

09979  *
09980  * GMX_RX_BP_ON = Hiwater mark for port/interface backpressure
09981  *
09982  *
09983  * Notes:
09984  * In XAUI mode, prt0 is used for checking.
09985  *
09986  */

09993                                                          Each register is for an individual port.  In XAUI
09994                                                          mode, prt0 is used for the unified RX FIFO

09996                                                          BP_OFF <= BP_ON < (FIFO_SIZE - BP_DROP)

10008                                                          In RGMII mode, the backpressure is given per
10009                                                          port.  In Spi4 mode, the backpressure is for the
10010                                                          entire interface.  GMX_RX_BP_ON must satisfy
10011                                                          BP_OFF <= BP_ON < (FIFO_SIZE - BP_DROP)
10012                                                          The reset value is half the FIFO.
10013                                                          Reset value RGMII mode = 0x40  (512bytes)
10014                                                          Reset value Spi4 mode  = 0x100 (2048bytes)
10015                                                          A value of zero will immediately assert back
10016                                                          pressure. */
10017 #else

10019     uint64_t reserved_9_63                : 55;
10020 #endif
10021     } cn30xx;

10089 /**
10090  * cvmx_gmx#_rx_pass_en
10091  *
10092  * GMX_RX_PASS_EN = Packet pass through mode enable
10093  *
10094  * When both Octane ports are running in Spi4 mode, packets can be directly
10095  * passed from one SPX interface to the other without being processed by the
10096  * core or PP's.  The register has one bit for each port to enable the pass
10097  * through feature.
10098  *
10099  * Notes:
10100  * (1) Can only be used in dual Spi4 configs
10101  *
10102  * (2) The mapped pass through output port cannot be the destination port for
10103  *     any Octane core traffic.
10104  */

10110     uint64_t en                           : 16; /**< Which ports to configure in pass through mode */
10111 #else
10112     uint64_t en                           : 16;
10113     uint64_t reserved_16_63               : 48;
10114 #endif
10115     } s;
10116     struct cvmx_gmxx_rx_pass_en_s         cn38xx;

10393                                                          0=Interleave lanes before PCS layer
10394                                                          As described in the Dune Networks/Broadcom
10395                                                          RXAUI v2.1 specification.
10396                                                          (obeys 6.25GHz SERDES disparity)
10397                                                          1=Interleave lanes after PCS layer
10398                                                          As described in the Marvell RXAUI Interface
10399                                                          specification.
10400                                                          (does not obey 6.25GHz SERDES disparity)
10401                                                          (RXAUI mode only) */
10402 #else
10403     uint64_t disparity                    : 1;
10404     uint64_t reserved_1_63                : 63;
10405 #endif
10406     } s;
10407     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxaui_ctl_s          cn68xx;
10408     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxaui_ctl_s          cn68xxp1;
10409     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxaui_ctl_s          cn70xx;
10410     struct cvmx_gmxx_rxaui_ctl_s          cn70xxp1;

10485 /**
10486  * cvmx_gmx#_stat_bp
10487  *
10488  * GMX_STAT_BP = Number of cycles that the TX/Stats block has help up operation
10489  *
10490  *
10491  * Notes:
10492  * It has no relationship with the TX FIFO per se.  The TX engine sends packets
10493  * from PKO and upon completion, sends a command to the TX stats block for an
10494  * update based on the packet size.  The stats operation can take a few cycles -
10495  * normally not enough to be visible considering the 64B min packet size that is
10496  * ethernet convention.
10497  *
10498  * In the rare case in which SW attempted to schedule really, really, small packets
10499  * or the sclk (6xxx) is running ass-slow, then the stats updates may not happen in
10500  * real time and can back up the TX engine.
10501  *
10502  * This counter is the number of cycles in which the TX engine was stalled.  In
10503  * normal operation, it should always be zeros.
10504  */
10505 union cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp {
10506     uint64_t u64;
10507     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s {
10508 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
10509     uint64_t reserved_17_63               : 47;
10510     uint64_t bp                           : 1;  /**< Current TX stats BP state
10511                                                          When the TX stats machine cannot update the stats
10512                                                          registers quickly enough, the machine has the
10513                                                          ability to BP TX datapath.  This is a rare event
10514                                                          and will not occur in normal operation.
10515                                                          0 = no backpressure is applied
10516                                                          1 = backpressure is applied to TX datapath to
10517                                                              allow stat update operations to complete */
10518     uint64_t cnt                          : 16; /**< Number of cycles that BP has been asserted
10519                                                          Saturating counter */
10520 #else
10521     uint64_t cnt                          : 16;
10522     uint64_t bp                           : 1;
10523     uint64_t reserved_17_63               : 47;
10524 #endif
10525     } s;
10526     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn30xx;
10527     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn31xx;
10528     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn38xx;
10529     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn38xxp2;
10530     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn50xx;
10531     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn52xx;
10532     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn52xxp1;
10533     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn56xx;
10534     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn56xxp1;
10535     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn58xx;
10536     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn58xxp1;
10537     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn61xx;
10538     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn63xx;
10539     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn63xxp1;
10540     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn66xx;
10541     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn68xx;
10542     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn68xxp1;
10543     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn70xx;
10544     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cn70xxp1;
10545     struct cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_s            cnf71xx;
10546 };
10547 typedef union cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp cvmx_gmxx_stat_bp_t;

10759 /**
10760  * cvmx_gmx#_tx#_clk
10761  *
10762  * Per Port
10763  *
10764  *
10765  * GMX_TX_CLK = RGMII TX Clock Generation Register
10766  *
10767  * Notes:
10768  * Programming Restrictions:
10769  *  (1) In RGMII mode, if GMX_PRT_CFG[SPEED]==0, then CLK_CNT must be > 1.
10770  *  (2) In MII mode, CLK_CNT == 1
10771  *  (3) In RGMII or GMII mode, if CLK_CNT==0, Octeon will not generate a tx clock.
10772  *
10773  * RGMII Example:
10774  *  Given a 125MHz PLL reference clock...
10775  *   CLK_CNT ==  1 ==> 125.0MHz TXC clock period (8ns* 1)
10776  *   CLK_CNT ==  5 ==>  25.0MHz TXC clock period (8ns* 5)
10777  *   CLK_CNT == 50 ==>   2.5MHz TXC clock period (8ns*50)
10778  */
10779 union cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk {
10780     uint64_t u64;
10781     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk_s {
10782 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
10783     uint64_t reserved_6_63                : 58;
10784     uint64_t clk_cnt                      : 6;  /**< Controls the RGMII TXC frequency
10785                                                          When PLL is used, TXC(phase) =
10786                                                           spi4_tx_pll_ref_clk(period)/2*CLK_CNT
10787                                                          When PLL bypass is used, TXC(phase) =
10788                                                           spi4_tx_pll_ref_clk(period)*2*CLK_CNT
10789                                                          NOTE: CLK_CNT==0 will not generate any clock
10790                                                          if CLK_CNT > 1 if GMX_PRT_CFG[SPEED]==0 */
10791 #else
10792     uint64_t clk_cnt                      : 6;
10793     uint64_t reserved_6_63                : 58;
10794 #endif
10795     } s;
10796     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk_s            cn30xx;
10797     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk_s            cn31xx;
10798     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk_s            cn38xx;
10799     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk_s            cn38xxp2;
10800     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk_s            cn50xx;
10801     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk_s            cn58xx;
10802     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk_s            cn58xxp1;
10803 };
10804 typedef union cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk cvmx_gmxx_txx_clk_t;

10925 /**
10926  * cvmx_gmx#_tx#_pause_pkt_interval
10927  *
10928  * GMX_TX_PAUSE_PKT_INTERVAL = Packet TX Pause Packet transmission interval - how often PAUSE packets will be sent
10929  *
10930  *
10931  * Notes:
10932  * Choosing proper values of GMX_TX_PAUSE_PKT_TIME[TIME] and
10933  * GMX_TX_PAUSE_PKT_INTERVAL[INTERVAL] can be challenging to the system
10934  * designer.  It is suggested that TIME be much greater than INTERVAL and
10935  * GMX_TX_PAUSE_ZERO[SEND] be set.  This allows a periodic refresh of the PAUSE
10936  * count and then when the backpressure condition is lifted, a PAUSE packet
10937  * with TIME==0 will be sent indicating that Octane is ready for additional
10938  * data.
10939  *
10940  * If the system chooses to not set GMX_TX_PAUSE_ZERO[SEND], then it is
10941  * suggested that TIME and INTERVAL are programmed such that they satisify the
10942  * following rule...
10943  *
10944  *    INTERVAL <= TIME - (largest_pkt_size + IFG + pause_pkt_size)
10945  *
10946  * where largest_pkt_size is that largest packet that the system can send
10947  * (normally 1518B), IFG is the interframe gap and pause_pkt_size is the size
10948  * of the PAUSE packet (normally 64B).
10949  */
10950 union cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval {
10951     uint64_t u64;
10952     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s {
10953 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
10954     uint64_t reserved_16_63               : 48;
10955     uint64_t interval                     : 16; /**< Arbitrate for a 802.3 pause packet, HiGig2 message,
10956                                                          or CBFC pause packet every (INTERVAL*512)
10957                                                          bit-times.
10958                                                          Normally, 0 < INTERVAL < GMX_TX_PAUSE_PKT_TIME
10959                                                          INTERVAL=0, will only send a single PAUSE packet
10960                                                          for each backpressure event */
10961 #else
10962     uint64_t interval                     : 16;
10963     uint64_t reserved_16_63               : 48;
10964 #endif
10965     } s;
10966     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn30xx;
10967     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn31xx;
10968     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn38xx;
10969     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn38xxp2;
10970     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn50xx;
10971     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn52xx;
10972     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn52xxp1;
10973     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn56xx;
10974     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn56xxp1;
10975     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn58xx;
10976     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn58xxp1;
10977     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn61xx;
10978     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn63xx;
10979     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn63xxp1;
10980     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn66xx;
10981     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn68xx;
10982     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn68xxp1;
10983     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn70xx;
10984     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cn70xxp1;
10985     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_s cnf71xx;
10986 };
10987 typedef union cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval cvmx_gmxx_txx_pause_pkt_interval_t;

11147  * cvmx_gmx#_tx#_pipe
11148  */
11149 union cvmx_gmxx_txx_pipe {
11150     uint64_t u64;
11151     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_pipe_s {
11152 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
11153     uint64_t reserved_33_63               : 31;
11154     uint64_t ign_bp                       : 1;  /**< When set, GMX will not throttle the TX machines
11155                                                          if the PIPE return FIFO fills up.
11156                                                          IGN_BP should be clear in normal operation. */
11157     uint64_t reserved_21_31               : 11;
11158     uint64_t nump                         : 5;  /**< Number of pipes this port|channel supports.
11159                                                          In SGMII mode, each port binds to one pipe.
11160                                                          In XAUI/RXAUI mode, the port can bind upto 16
11161                                                          consecutive pipes.
11162                                                          SGMII      mode, NUMP = 0 or 1.
11163                                                          XAUI/RXAUI mode, NUMP = 0 or 1-16.
11164                                                          0 = Disabled */
11165     uint64_t reserved_7_15                : 9;
11166     uint64_t base                         : 7;  /**< When NUMP is non-zero, indicates the base pipe
11167                                                          number this port|channel will accept.
11168                                                          This port will accept pko packets from pipes in
11169                                                          the range of:
11170                                                            BASE .. (BASE+(NUMP-1))
11171                                                          BASE and NUMP must be constrained such that
11172                                                            1) BASE+(NUMP-1) < 127
11173                                                            2) Each used PKO pipe must map to exactly
11174                                                               one port|channel
11175                                                            3) The pipe ranges must be consistent with
11176                                                               the PKO configuration. */
11177 #else
11178     uint64_t base                         : 7;
11179     uint64_t reserved_7_15                : 9;
11180     uint64_t nump                         : 5;
11181     uint64_t reserved_21_31               : 11;
11182     uint64_t ign_bp                       : 1;
11183     uint64_t reserved_33_63               : 31;
11184 #endif
11185     } s;

11193  */
11194 union cvmx_gmxx_txx_sgmii_ctl {
11195     uint64_t u64;
11196     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_sgmii_ctl_s {
11197 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
11198     uint64_t reserved_1_63                : 63;
11199     uint64_t align                        : 1;  /**< Align the transmission to even cycles
11200 
11201                                                          Recommended value is:
11202                                                             ALIGN = !GMX_TX_APPEND[PREAMBLE]
11203 
11204                                                          (See the Transmit Conversion to Code groups
11205                                                           section in the SGMII Interface chapter of the
11206                                                           HRM for a complete discussion)
11207 
11208                                                          0 = Data can be sent on any cycle
11209                                                              In this mode, the interface will function at
11210                                                              maximum bandwidth. It is possible to for the
11211                                                              TX PCS machine to drop first byte of the TX
11212                                                              frame.  When GMX_TX_APPEND[PREAMBLE] is set,
11213                                                              the first byte will be a preamble byte which
11214                                                              can be dropped to compensate for an extended
11215                                                              IPG.
11216 
11217                                                          1 = Data will only be sent on even cycles.
11218                                                              In this mode, there can be bandwidth
11219                                                              implications when sending odd-byte packets as
11220                                                              the IPG can extend an extra cycle.
11221                                                              There will be no loss of data.
11222 
11223                                                          (SGMII/1000Base-X only) */
11224 #else
11225     uint64_t align                        : 1;
11226     uint64_t reserved_1_63                : 63;
11227 #endif
11228     } s;

11675  * - Cleared either by a write (of any value) or a read when GMX_TX_STATS_CTL[RD_CLR] is set
11676  * - Counters will wrap
11677  */
11678 union cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7 {
11679     uint64_t u64;
11680     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s {
11681 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
11682     uint64_t hist7                        : 32; /**< Number of packets sent with an octet count
11683                                                          of > 1518. */
11684     uint64_t hist6                        : 32; /**< Number of packets sent with an octet count of
11685                                                          1024 - 1518. */
11686 #else
11687     uint64_t hist6                        : 32;
11688     uint64_t hist7                        : 32;
11689 #endif
11690     } s;
11691     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn30xx;
11692     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn31xx;
11693     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn38xx;
11694     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn38xxp2;
11695     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn50xx;
11696     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn52xx;
11697     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn52xxp1;
11698     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn56xx;
11699     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn56xxp1;
11700     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn58xx;
11701     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat7_s          cn58xxp1;

11714 /**
11715  * cvmx_gmx#_tx#_stat8
11716  *
11717  * GMX_TX_STAT8 = GMX_TX_STATS_MCST  / GMX_TX_STATS_BCST
11718  *
11719  *
11720  * Notes:
11721  * - Cleared either by a write (of any value) or a read when GMX_TX_STATS_CTL[RD_CLR] is set
11722  * - Counters will wrap
11723  * - Note, GMX determines if the packet is MCST or BCST from the DMAC of the
11724  *   packet.  GMX assumes that the DMAC lies in the first 6 bytes of the packet
11725  *   as per the 802.3 frame definition.  If the system requires additional data
11726  *   before the L2 header, then the MCST and BCST counters may not reflect
11727  *   reality and should be ignored by software.
11728  */
11729 union cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8 {

11731     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s {
11732 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD

11734                                                          Does not include BCST packets. */
11735     uint64_t bcst                         : 32; /**< Number of packets sent to broadcast DMAC.
11736                                                          Does not include MCST packets. */
11737 #else
11738     uint64_t bcst                         : 32;
11739     uint64_t mcst                         : 32;
11740 #endif
11741     } s;
11742     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn30xx;
11743     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn31xx;
11744     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn38xx;
11745     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn38xxp2;
11746     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn50xx;
11747     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn52xx;
11748     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn52xxp1;
11749     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn56xx;
11750     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn56xxp1;
11751     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn58xx;
11752     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn58xxp1;
11753     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_stat8_s          cn61xx;

11854 /**

11856  *
11857  * Per Port
11858  * GMX_TX_THRESH = Packet TX Threshold
11859  */
11860 union cvmx_gmxx_txx_thresh {
11861     uint64_t u64;
11862     struct cvmx_gmxx_txx_thresh_s {
11863 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
11864     uint64_t reserved_10_63               : 54;
11865     uint64_t cnt                          : 10; /**< Number of 16B ticks to accumulate in the TX FIFO
11866                                                          before sending on the packet interface
11867                                                          This register should be large enough to prevent
11868                                                          underflow on the packet interface and must never
11869                                                          be set to zero.  This register cannot exceed the
11870                                                          the TX FIFO depth which is...
11871                                                           GMX_TX_PRTS==0,1:  CNT MAX = 0x100
11872                                                           GMX_TX_PRTS==2  :  CNT MAX = 0x080
11873                                                           GMX_TX_PRTS==3,4:  CNT MAX = 0x040 */
11874 #else
11875     uint64_t cnt                          : 10;
11876     uint64_t reserved_10_63               : 54;
11877 #endif
11878     } s;

11880 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
11881     uint64_t reserved_7_63                : 57;
11882     uint64_t cnt                          : 7;  /**< Number of 16B ticks to accumulate in the TX FIFO
11883                                                          before sending on the RGMII interface
11884                                                          This register should be large enough to prevent
11885                                                          underflow on the RGMII interface and must never
11886                                                          be set below 4.  This register cannot exceed the
11887                                                          the TX FIFO depth which is 64 16B entries. */
11888 #else
11889     uint64_t cnt                          : 7;
11890     uint64_t reserved_7_63                : 57;
11891 #endif
11892     } cn30xx;

11895 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
11896     uint64_t reserved_9_63                : 55;
11897     uint64_t cnt                          : 9;  /**< Number of 16B ticks to accumulate in the TX FIFO
11898                                                           before sending on the RGMII interface
11899                                                           This register should be large enough to prevent
11900                                                           underflow on the RGMII interface and must never
11901                                                           be set to zero.  This register cannot exceed the
11902                                                           the TX FIFO depth which is...
11903                                                            GMX_TX_PRTS==0,1:  CNT MAX = 0x100
11904                                                            GMX_TX_PRTS==2  :  CNT MAX = 0x080
11905                                                            GMX_TX_PRTS==3,4:  CNT MAX = 0x040
11906                                                          (PASS2 expands from 6 to 9 bits) */
11907 #else

12061 /**
12062  * cvmx_gmx#_tx_corrupt
12063  *
12064  * GMX_TX_CORRUPT = TX - Corrupt TX packets with the ERR bit set
12065  *
12066  *
12067  * Notes:
12068  * Packets sent from PKO with the ERR wire asserted will be corrupted by
12069  * the transmitter if CORRUPT[prt] is set (XAUI uses prt==0).
12070  *
12071  * Corruption means that GMX will send a bad FCS value.  If GMX_TX_APPEND[FCS]
12072  * is clear then no FCS is sent and the GMX cannot corrupt it.  The corrupt FCS
12073  * value is 0xeeeeeeee for SGMII/1000Base-X and 4 bytes of the error
12074  * propagation code in XAUI mode.
12075  */
12076 union cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt {
12077     uint64_t u64;
12078     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_s {
12079 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
12080     uint64_t reserved_4_63                : 60;
12081     uint64_t corrupt                      : 4;  /**< Per port error propagation
12082                                                          0=Never corrupt packets
12083                                                          1=Corrupt packets with ERR */
12084 #else
12085     uint64_t corrupt                      : 4;
12086     uint64_t reserved_4_63                : 60;
12087 #endif
12088     } s;
12089     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_cn30xx {
12090 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
12091     uint64_t reserved_3_63                : 61;
12092     uint64_t corrupt                      : 3;  /**< Per port error propagation
12093                                                          0=Never corrupt packets
12094                                                          1=Corrupt packets with ERR */
12095 #else
12096     uint64_t corrupt                      : 3;
12097     uint64_t reserved_3_63                : 61;
12098 #endif
12099     } cn30xx;
12100     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_cn30xx    cn31xx;
12101     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_s         cn38xx;
12102     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_s         cn38xxp2;
12103     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_cn30xx    cn50xx;
12104     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_s         cn52xx;
12105     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_s         cn52xxp1;
12106     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_s         cn56xx;
12107     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_s         cn56xxp1;
12108     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_corrupt_s         cn58xx;

12132 /**
12133  * cvmx_gmx#_tx_hg2_reg1
12134  *
12135  * Notes:
12136  * The TX_XOF[15:0] field in GMX(0)_TX_HG2_REG1 and the TX_XON[15:0] field in
12137  * GMX(0)_TX_HG2_REG2 register map to the same 16 physical flops. When written with address of
12138  * GMX(0)_TX_HG2_REG1, it will exhibit write 1 to set behavior and when written with address of
12139  * GMX(0)_TX_HG2_REG2, it will exhibit write 1 to clear behavior.
12140  * For reads, either address will return the $GMX(0)_TX_HG2_REG1 values.
12141  */
12142 union cvmx_gmxx_tx_hg2_reg1 {
12143     uint64_t u64;
12144     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_hg2_reg1_s {
12145 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
12146     uint64_t reserved_16_63               : 48;
12147     uint64_t tx_xof                       : 16; /**< TX HiGig2 message for logical link pause when any
12148                                                          bit value changes
12149                                                           Only write in HiGig2 mode i.e. when
12150                                                           GMX_TX_XAUI_CTL[HG_EN]=1 and
12151                                                           GMX_RX_UDD_SKP[LEN]=16. */
12152 #else
12153     uint64_t tx_xof                       : 16;
12154     uint64_t reserved_16_63               : 48;
12155 #endif
12156     } s;
12157     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_hg2_reg1_s        cn52xx;

12212 /**
12213  * cvmx_gmx#_tx_ifg
12214  *
12215  * GMX_TX_IFG = Packet TX Interframe Gap
12216  *
12217  *
12218  * Notes:
12219  * * Programming IFG1 and IFG2.
12220  *
12221  * For 10/100/1000Mbs half-duplex systems that require IEEE 802.3
12222  * compatibility, IFG1 must be in the range of 1-8, IFG2 must be in the range
12223  * of 4-12, and the IFG1+IFG2 sum must be 12.
12224  *
12225  * For 10/100/1000Mbs full-duplex systems that require IEEE 802.3
12226  * compatibility, IFG1 must be in the range of 1-11, IFG2 must be in the range
12227  * of 1-11, and the IFG1+IFG2 sum must be 12.
12228  *
12229  * For XAUI/10Gbs systems that require IEEE 802.3 compatibility, the
12230  * IFG1+IFG2 sum must be 12.  IFG1[1:0] and IFG2[1:0] must be zero.
12231  *
12232  * For all other systems, IFG1 and IFG2 can be any value in the range of
12233  * 1-15.  Allowing for a total possible IFG sum of 2-30.
12234  */
12235 union cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg {
12236     uint64_t u64;
12237     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s {
12238 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
12239     uint64_t reserved_8_63                : 56;
12240     uint64_t ifg2                         : 4;  /**< 1/3 of the interframe gap timing (in IFG2*8 bits)
12241                                                          If CRS is detected during IFG2, then the
12242                                                          interFrameSpacing timer is not reset and a frame
12243                                                          is transmited once the timer expires. */
12244     uint64_t ifg1                         : 4;  /**< 2/3 of the interframe gap timing (in IFG1*8 bits)
12245                                                          If CRS is detected during IFG1, then the
12246                                                          interFrameSpacing timer is reset and a frame is
12247                                                          not transmited. */
12248 #else
12249     uint64_t ifg1                         : 4;
12250     uint64_t ifg2                         : 4;
12251     uint64_t reserved_8_63                : 56;
12252 #endif
12253     } s;
12254     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn30xx;
12255     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn31xx;
12256     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn38xx;
12257     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn38xxp2;
12258     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn50xx;
12259     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn52xx;
12260     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn52xxp1;
12261     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn56xx;
12262     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn56xxp1;
12263     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn58xx;
12264     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn58xxp1;
12265     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn61xx;
12266     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn63xx;
12267     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn63xxp1;
12268     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn66xx;
12269     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn68xx;
12270     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn68xxp1;
12271     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn70xx;
12272     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cn70xxp1;
12273     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ifg_s             cnf71xx;

12893 /**
12894  * cvmx_gmx#_tx_ovr_bp
12895  *
12896  * GMX_TX_OVR_BP = Packet Interface TX Override BackPressure
12897  *
12898  *
12899  * Notes:
12900  * In XAUI mode, only the lsb (corresponding to port0) of EN, BP, and IGN_FULL are used.
12901  *
12902  * GMX*_TX_OVR_BP[EN<0>] must be set to one and GMX*_TX_OVR_BP[BP<0>] must be cleared to zero
12903  * (to forcibly disable HW-automatic 802.3 pause packet generation) with the HiGig2 Protocol
12904  * when GMX*_HG2_CONTROL[HG2TX_EN]=0. (The HiGig2 protocol is indicated by
12905  * GMX*_TX_XAUI_CTL[HG_EN]=1 and GMX*_RX0_UDD_SKP[LEN]=16.) HW can only auto-generate backpressure
12906  * through HiGig2 messages (optionally, when GMX*_HG2_CONTROL[HG2TX_EN]=1) with the HiGig2
12907  * protocol.
12908  */
12909 union cvmx_gmxx_tx_ovr_bp {
12910     uint64_t u64;
12911     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ovr_bp_s {
12912 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
12913     uint64_t reserved_48_63               : 16;
12914     uint64_t tx_prt_bp                    : 16; /**< Per port BP sent to PKO
12915                                                          0=Port is available
12916                                                          1=Port should be back pressured
12917                                                          TX_PRT_BP should not be set until
12918                                                          GMX_INF_MODE[EN] has been enabled */
12919     uint64_t reserved_12_31               : 20;
12920     uint64_t en                           : 4;  /**< Per port Enable back pressure override */
12921     uint64_t bp                           : 4;  /**< Per port BackPressure status to use
12922                                                          0=Port is available
12923                                                          1=Port should be back pressured */
12924     uint64_t ign_full                     : 4;  /**< Ignore the RX FIFO full when computing BP */
12925 #else
12926     uint64_t ign_full                     : 4;
12927     uint64_t bp                           : 4;
12928     uint64_t en                           : 4;
12929     uint64_t reserved_12_31               : 20;
12930     uint64_t tx_prt_bp                    : 16;
12931     uint64_t reserved_48_63               : 16;
12932 #endif
12933     } s;
12934     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ovr_bp_cn30xx {
12935 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
12936     uint64_t reserved_11_63               : 53;
12937     uint64_t en                           : 3;  /**< Per port Enable back pressure override */
12938     uint64_t reserved_7_7                 : 1;
12939     uint64_t bp                           : 3;  /**< Per port BackPressure status to use
12940                                                          0=Port is available
12941                                                          1=Port should be back pressured */
12942     uint64_t reserved_3_3                 : 1;
12943     uint64_t ign_full                     : 3;  /**< Ignore the RX FIFO full when computing BP */
12944 #else
12945     uint64_t ign_full                     : 3;
12946     uint64_t reserved_3_3                 : 1;
12947     uint64_t bp                           : 3;
12948     uint64_t reserved_7_7                 : 1;
12949     uint64_t en                           : 3;
12950     uint64_t reserved_11_63               : 53;
12951 #endif
12952     } cn30xx;
12953     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ovr_bp_cn30xx     cn31xx;
12954     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_ovr_bp_cn38xx {
12955 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
12956     uint64_t reserved_12_63               : 52;
12957     uint64_t en                           : 4;  /**< Per port Enable back pressure override */
12958     uint64_t bp                           : 4;  /**< Per port BackPressure status to use
12959                                                          0=Port is available
12960                                                          1=Port should be back pressured */

13204     uint64_t reserved_23_63               : 41;
13205     uint64_t slice                        : 7;  /**< Number of 16B blocks to transmit in a burst before
13206                                                          switching to the next port. SLICE does not always
13207                                                          limit the burst length transmitted by OCTEON.
13208                                                          Depending on the traffic pattern and
13209                                                          GMX_TX_SPI_ROUND programming, the next port could
13210                                                          be the same as the current port. In this case,
13211                                                          OCTEON may merge multiple sub-SLICE bursts into
13212                                                          one contiguous burst that is longer than SLICE
13213                                                          (as long as the burst does not cross a packet
13214                                                          boundary).
13215                                                          SLICE must be programmed to be >=
13216                                                            GMX_TX_SPI_THRESH[THRESH]
13217                                                          If SLICE==0, then the transmitter will tend to
13218                                                          send the complete packet. The port will only
13219                                                          switch if credits are exhausted or PKO cannot
13220                                                          keep up.
13221                                                          (90nm ONLY) */
13222     uint64_t max2                         : 8;  /**< MAX2 (per Spi4.2 spec) */
13223     uint64_t max1                         : 8;  /**< MAX1 (per Spi4.2 spec)
13224                                                          MAX1 >= GMX_TX_SPI_THRESH[THRESH] */
13225 #else
13226     uint64_t max1                         : 8;

13230 #endif
13231     } s;

13236     uint64_t max1                         : 8;  /**< MAX1 (per Spi4.2 spec)

13276 /**
13277  * cvmx_gmx#_tx_spi_thresh
13278  *
13279  * GMX_TX_SPI_THRESH = RGMII TX Spi4 Transmit Threshold
13280  *
13281  *
13282  * Notes:
13283  * Note: zero will map to 0x20
13284  *
13285  * This will normally creates Spi4 traffic bursts at least THRESH in length.
13286  * If dclk > eclk, then this rule may not always hold and Octeon may split
13287  * transfers into smaller bursts - some of which could be as short as 16B.
13288  * Octeon will never violate the Spi4.2 spec and send a non-EOP burst that is
13289  * not a multiple of 16B.
13290  */
13291 union cvmx_gmxx_tx_spi_thresh {
13292     uint64_t u64;
13293     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_spi_thresh_s {
13294 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
13295     uint64_t reserved_6_63                : 58;
13296     uint64_t thresh                       : 6;  /**< Transmit threshold in 16B blocks - cannot be zero
13297                                                          THRESH <= TX_FIFO size   (in non-passthrough mode)
13298                                                          THRESH <= TX_FIFO size-2 (in passthrough mode)
13299                                                          THRESH <= GMX_TX_SPI_MAX[MAX1]
13300                                                          THRESH <= GMX_TX_SPI_MAX[MAX2], if not then is it
13301                                                           possible for Octeon to send a Spi4 data burst of
13302                                                           MAX2 <= burst <= THRESH 16B ticks
13303                                                          GMX_TX_SPI_MAX[SLICE] must be programmed to be >=
13304                                                            THRESH */
13305 #else
13306     uint64_t thresh                       : 6;
13307     uint64_t reserved_6_63                : 58;
13308 #endif
13309     } s;
13310     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_spi_thresh_s      cn38xx;
13311     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_spi_thresh_s      cn38xxp2;
13312     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_spi_thresh_s      cn58xx;
13313     struct cvmx_gmxx_tx_spi_thresh_s      cn58xxp1;
13314 };
13315 typedef union cvmx_gmxx_tx_spi_thresh cvmx_gmxx_tx_spi_thresh_t;

13366                                                          (XAUI mode only) */
13367 #else
